            <div id="content">
                <h1 class="centered">Privacy Policy</h1>
                <div>
                    <div>
                        <h2>Effective Date</h2>
                        <p>
                            The effective date for this policy is October 3, 2012.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="separator"></div>
                    <div>
                        <h2 id="personal-info">Personal info</h2>
                        <p>
                            We collect no directly identifiable personal information from players of our games. User
                            logins are only used to associate a specific player with a specific game and to show users
                            what games in which they are currently active. These logins have no explicit link to a
                            user's email or any other indicator.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="separator"></div>
                    <div>
                        <h2 id="collection">How we collect info</h2>
                        <h3 id="collection_tracking">Tracking technologies</h3>
                        <h4>Do we use cookies?</h4>
                        <p>
                            Yes. (Cookies are small files that a site or its service provider transfers to your computers
                            hard drive through your Web browser (if you allow) that enables the sites or service providers
                            systems to recognize your browser and capture and remember certain information.
                        </p>
                        <h4>What else do we use?</h4>
                        <p>
                            We collect information from our players by means Adobe's Blaze Data Services (BlazeDS) and
                            its interactions with our Flash Client.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="separator"></div>
                    <div>
                        <h2 id="use">How we use your info</h2>
                        <p>
                            Cookies are used by JBoss's JAAS authentication system to determine if a player has
                            authenticated properly. The information collected through interactions among our Flash
                            Client, BlazeDS and our JEE application in order to understand strategic user game play in
                            our research.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="separator"></div>
                    <div>
                        <h2 id="disclosure">When we share your info</h2>
                        <p>
                            We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer to outside parties your personally identifiable
                            information. This does not include trusted third parties who assist us in operating our
                            website, conducting our business, or servicing you, so long as those parties agree to keep
                            this information confidential. We may also release your information when we believe release
                            is appropriate to comply with the law, enforce our site policies, or protect ours or others
                            rights, property, or safety.
                        </p>
                        <h3>California Online Privacy Protection Act Compliance</h3>
                        <p>
                            Because we value your privacy we have taken the necessary precautions to be in compliance
                            with the California Online Privacy Protection Act. We therefore will not distribute your
                            personal information to outside parties without your consent.
                        </p>
                        <h3>United States Children's Online Privacy Protection Act Compliance</h3>
                        <p>
                            We are in compliance with the requirements of the United States COPPA (Childrens Online
                            Privacy Protection Act), we do not collect any information from anyone under 13 years of
                            age. Our website, products and services are all directed to people who are at least 13
                            years old or older.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="separator"></div>
                    <div>
                        <h2 id="storage">How we store your info</h2>
                        <h3 id="storage_location">Where your info lives</h3>
                        <p>
                            Your information lives inside of a MySQL database secured against outside connectivity.
                        </p>
                        <h3 id="storage_duration">How long we keep your info</h3>
                        <p>
                            We keep all information recorded in our database for an indefinite period of time,
                            determined solely by its utility to our ongoing research.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="separator"></div>
                    <div>
                        <h2 id="misc">About</h2>
                        <h3 id="misc_choice">Your choices</h3>
                        <p>
                            You are free to not login and play our games if you feel playing our games should remain
                            a private experience.
                        </p>
                        <h3 id="misc_changes">Changes</h3>
                        <p>
                            This privacy policy is subject to update, with any such changes being published here.
                        </p>
